extremeCfgMgmt.name: extremeCfgMgmt
extremeCfgMgmt.description: Extreme Configuration Management objects: objects common to all platforms

extremeLastSaveCfgTable.name: extremeLastSaveCfgTable
extremeLastSaveCfgTable.description: This group of objects contain details of the last saved configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

extremeLastSavedEntry.name: extremeLastSavedEntry
extremeLastSavedEntry.description: This group of objects contain details of the last saved configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

extremeLastSaveConfigSlotId.name: extremeLastSaveConfigSlotId
extremeLastSaveConfigSlotId.description: Specifies the MSM/MM module number of a switch or the slot number currently being used by the active stack node.

extremeLastSaveConfigTime.name: extremeLastSaveConfigTime
extremeLastSaveConfigTime.description: This object will return the date and time of the last configuration save operation. This data will reflect the last cli or the last setting of the extremeSaveConfiguration object.

extremeLastSaveConfigFileName.name: extremeLastSaveConfigFileName
extremeLastSaveConfigFileName.description: This object will return the configuration file name of the last save operation.

extremeLastSaveConfigSource.name: extremeLastSaveConfigSource
extremeLastSaveConfigSource.description: This object indicates the source of the last configuration save operation for the configuration file associated with this entry, extremeLastSaveConfigFileName .

extremeLastChangeCfgTable.name: extremeLastChangeCfgTable
extremeLastChangeCfgTable.description: This group of objects contain details of the last change configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

extremeLastChangeCfgEntry.name: extremeLastChangeCfgEntry
extremeLastChangeCfgEntry.description: This group of objects contain details of the last change configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

extremeLastChangeCfgSlotId.name: extremeLastChangeCfgSlotId
extremeLastChangeCfgSlotId.description: Specifies the MSM/MM module number of a switch or the slot number currently being used by the active stack node.

extremeLastChangeConfigTime.name: extremeLastChangeConfigTime
extremeLastChangeConfigTime.description: This object will return the date and time of the last configuration change operation. This data will reflect the last cli or the last setting of the extremeSaveConfiguration object.

extremeLastChangeConfigFileName.name: extremeLastChangeConfigFileName
extremeLastChangeConfigFileName.description: This object will return the configuration file name of the last change operation.

extremeLastChangeConfigSource.name: extremeLastChangeConfigSource
extremeLastChangeConfigSource.description: This object indicates the source of the last configuration change operation for extremeLastChangeConfigFileName .

extremeRunningLastSavedCfgGroup.name: extremeRunningLastSavedCfgGroup
extremeRunningLastSavedCfgGroup.description: This group of objects contain details of the last saved configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

extremeRunningLastChangeCfgGroup.name: extremeRunningLastChangeCfgGroup
extremeRunningLastChangeCfgGroup.description: This group of objects contain details of the last change configuration operation for the running configure. If the value of extremeLastChangeConfigTime is greater than extremeLastSaveConfigTime, the configuration has been changed but not saved.

cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrapEnable.name: cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrapEnable
cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrap notification. A false value will prevent notifications from being generated by this system.

cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrapEnable.name: cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrapEnable
cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrap notification. A false value will prevent notifications from being generated by this system.

cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrap.name: cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrap
cfgMgmtConfigSaveTrap.description: This notification indicates that the running configuration of the managed system has updated the NVRAM storage of the current configuration.

cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrap.name: cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrap
cfgMgmtConfigChangeTrap.description: This notification contain details of the last change configuration operation for the running configure.
